50|$|The naming {{conventions}} of the Canadian Army can be confusing. Regular Force <b>armoured</b> and <b>infantry</b> units are not usually named for a location, because personnel are drawn from across the country. Artillery and engineer units are almost always numbered, but may have a distinctive nickname. Reserve <b>armoured</b> and <b>infantry</b> units generally are named, and may carry a number if it has historical significance. In wartime, units raised for the duration often are numbered.|$|R
