50|$|From the 1966-67 edition to the 1969-70 edition, the IISS Military Balance {{listed the}} Iranian Army with one <b>armoured</b> division, seven <b>infantry</b> divisions, and one {{independent}} armoured brigade. By the 1971-72 edition, two <b>armoured</b> divisions, five <b>infantry</b> divisions, the independent armoured brigade, and other independent brigades were listed. Within {{two years after}} that, the listing quickly changed to three armoured divisions and three infantry divisions.|$|R
